# Static Pods & kubeadm

## Static pods

> Kubelet runs them from **disk** — *no API server*. Watches `/etc/kubernetes/manifests`.

- Creates a **mirror pod** so `kubectl` sees it.
- **Can't `kubectl delete`** — recreated in seconds. **Move the manifest file.**
- Solves the **chicken-and-egg**: control plane holds `etcd.yaml`, `kube-apiserver.yaml`, … → **etcd first**.

## kubeadm — the installer

> **Doesn't** provision machines / OS / CNI. Two commands:

- **`kubeadm init`** — preflight → **PKI** → static manifests → CoreDNS + kube-proxy → print `join` + token.
- **`kubeadm join`** — token auth, verify CA hash, register Node.

> **CNI is your job** — Pods stay `Pending` until you apply one (Calico). Tokens **expire 24h**.
